q18.question: Why is Adrian suspected by the police?
q18.answer: ['speed drive', 'Because he ran away from the car with dead Guy']
q18.recall: Adrian is suspected by the police because he is found hiding in a synagogue and his eyes flash red, causing two kids to fall unconscious.
q18.vectordb: Adrian is suspected by the police because his fingerprints were found on a downed power line that was used to kill Peter. He is being held as a prisoner and is considered a suspect in the cataclysmic event that occurred during his birthday party. However, Adrian suffers from amnesia and does not remember the events clearly. It is later revealed that Adrian is being targeted by a coven who believes he is the son of Satan and they have plans for him. Guy Woodhouse, a member of the coven, fears Adrian and tries to get rid of him. Adrian escapes from the hospital with the help of a nurse named Ellen, who is also a member of the coven. Ellen drugs Adrian and reveals the coven's plan to start over with a new baby who will be raised as a vessel for Satan's child. However, their plan is disrupted when Ellen is run over by a car driven by Guy. Adrian, confused and scared, runs away. The film ends with the coven discussing their loss of control over Adrian but looking forward to their "new beginning."
q18.hybrid: Adrian is suspected by the police because he is found hiding in a synagogue and his eyes flash red, causing two kids to fall unconscious.
